      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Renew Claude web cookies",
        "body": "## Summary\n- renew Claude Web session keys from successful `Set-Cookie: sessionKey=...` responses\n- reuse a rotated session key for later requests in the same Web fetch\n- track renewal for manual cookie fetches too, while keeping manual cookies read-only so they do not rewrite cached browser-derived state\n\n## Root cause\nClaude Web usage requests reused a cached `sessionKey` but ignored `Set-Cookie` renewal headers from claude.ai. Once the cached key aged out, later refreshes could keep sending stale credentials. The first patch fixed browser/cache-backed fetches, but the manual-cookie path still skipped the renewal tracker because persistence provenance was also controlling in-memory renewal tracking.\n\n## Fix\n- create the renewal tracker for every Claude Web fetch\n- use the tracker's current session key for `/usage`, extra usage, and account calls\n- keep `CookieHeaderCache.store` gated on `cacheSourceLabel`, so only browser/cache-backed cookies are persisted\n- extend the manual-cookie regression test to assert that `/usage` receives the renewed key while the cached browser cookie remains unchanged\n\n## Proof\n- `swift test --filter ClaudeWebCookieRenewalTests`\n- `make check`\n- Redacted live Claude Web fetch on 2026-06-14 17:06 Pacific:\n  - browser cookie source found: Safari\n  - `/api/organizations` status: 200\n  - `/api/organizations/{org}/usage` status: 200\n  - cookie cache stored from Safari after the successful fetch\n- Redacted live header probe on 2026-06-14 17:06 Pacific:\n  - cached session fingerprint: `sha256:e42266eaa620`\n  - `/api/organizations` status: 200, `Set-Cookie` headers: 1, `sessionKey` renewal: no\n  - `/api/organizations/{org}/usage` status: 200, `Set-Cookie` headers: 1, `sessionKey` renewal: no\n  - no real `sessionKey` renewal was emitted by claude.ai during this run, so live renewed-key reuse could not be observed honestly; the renewal/reuse behavior is covered by the request-header regression tests above\n\nRefs #1287\n",
        "branch": "fix/claude-web-cookie-renewal",
